---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import PageHero from '../components/PageHero.astro';
import { site, telLandline, mailLink } from '../data/site';
---
<Layout
  current=""
  title="Terms & Conditions | The London Left Hand Drive Centre"
  description="The terms governing the sale and purchase of vehicles with the London LHD Centre."
>
  <PageHero
    eyebrow="Legal"
    title="Terms & Conditions"
    subtitle="The terms that apply when buying from or selling to us."
    crumb="Terms & Conditions"
  />

  <section class="py-24 md:py-32 bg-white">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <div class="legal-prose fade-in">
        <p><strong>Last updated:</strong> 02/06/2026</p>

        <h2>Introduction &amp; acceptance</h2>
        <p>
          These terms and conditions govern the sale and purchase of vehicles between you and
          {site.name}. By enquiring about, reserving, buying or selling a vehicle with us, you
          confirm that you have read, understood and accepted these terms. Please read them
          carefully. If there is anything you do not understand, contact us before you proceed.
        </p>

        <h2>About us</h2>
        <p>
          {site.name} is a specialist left-hand drive (LHD) car dealer operating from two London
          showrooms:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Barnes, London <strong>SW13 9JJ</strong> — our main showroom and inventory base.</li>
          <li>Chelsea Harbour, London <strong>SW10 0XG</strong> — our premium showroom, by appointment.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          You can reach us by email at <a href={mailLink}>{site.email}</a> or by telephone on
          <a href={telLandline}>{site.phoneLandline}</a>. Wherever these terms refer to "we", "us"
          or "our", they refer to {site.name}.
        </p>

        <h2>Vehicle descriptions &amp; availability</h2>
        <p>
          We strive for accuracy in every vehicle description, specification and price we publish.
          However, specifications and availability are subject to change, and details may be
          updated or corrected without notice. Photographs and images are for illustration only;
          the actual vehicle, its trim, colour and equipment may differ. Mileage, service history
          and condition are described to the best of our knowledge at the time of listing.
        </p>
        <p>
          A vehicle shown as available may be reserved or sold by the time you enquire, as our
          stock moves quickly. Please confirm all details, including specification and availability,
          with us directly before committing to a purchase.
        </p>

        <h2>Pricing</h2>
        <p>
          All prices are quoted in pounds sterling (£ GBP) and are subject to change. Prices
          include VAT where applicable, and any VAT position will be confirmed at the point of sale.
          Vehicles shown as "Call us", "POA" (price on application) or similar are priced by
          enquiry; please contact us for the current price. We reserve the right to correct any
          pricing errors, in which case we will let you know before the sale is concluded.
        </p>

        <h2>Deposits &amp; payment</h2>
        <p>
          We accept payment by cash, bank transfer or bankers' draft. Other payment arrangements
          may be available by agreement. A deposit is required to reserve a vehicle and to take it
          off sale. The balance is due in full, and cleared, before collection or delivery of the
          vehicle. A vehicle remains our property until payment has been received in full and has
          cleared.
        </p>

        <h2>Selling your car to us</h2>
        <p>
          If you are selling your left-hand drive car to us, we offer a free, no-obligation
          valuation. We may arrange an inspection of the vehicle before confirming our offer, and
          our offer is subject to that inspection and to the vehicle matching the description you
          have provided.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Any outstanding finance on the vehicle must be settled — we can usually help arrange this as part of the transaction.</li>
          <li>You must be the legal owner of the vehicle, or be authorised to sell it.</li>
          <li>The V5C registration document and all relevant paperwork, including service history and spare keys where available, must be provided.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Imported cars, UK registration &amp; COC papers</h2>
        <p>
          Many of the vehicles we handle are imported left-hand drive cars. Where a vehicle requires
          UK registration, we can assist with the process. A Certificate of Conformity (COC) and
          other supporting documentation may be required to register or re-register a vehicle.
          Responsibility for registration, timescales and any associated fees will be confirmed in
          writing for each transaction. Imported vehicles may be supplied registered or unregistered
          depending on the arrangement agreed with you.
        </p>

        <h2>Delivery &amp; collection</h2>
        <p>
          You are welcome to collect your vehicle from our Barnes showroom by appointment. We can
          also arrange delivery throughout the United Kingdom, Europe, the USA and the Middle East.
          Delivery is arranged by agreement, and any delivery costs, timescales and logistics will
          be confirmed before your purchase is finalised. Risk in the vehicle passes to you on
          collection or delivery.
        </p>

        <h2>Your statutory rights</h2>
        <p>
          Nothing in these terms affects your statutory rights as a consumer. Where you buy as a
          consumer, your rights under the Consumer Rights Act 2015 — including those relating to
          goods being of satisfactory quality, fit for purpose and as described — remain unaffected.
        </p>

        <h2>Limitation of liability</h2>
        <p>
          We do not exclude or limit our liability to you where it would be unlawful to do so. This
          includes liability for death or personal injury caused by our negligence, for fraud or
          fraudulent misrepresentation, or for any other liability that cannot be excluded under
          law. Subject to that, we will not be liable for any indirect or consequential loss, and
          our total liability arising from any transaction will not exceed the price paid for the
          vehicle concerned.
        </p>

        <h2>Governing law</h2>
        <p>
          These terms, and any dispute or claim arising out of or in connection with them or their
          subject matter, are governed by and construed in accordance with the law of England and
          Wales, and are subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of England and Wales.
        </p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>
          If you have any questions about these terms, please contact {site.name} by email at
          <a href={mailLink}>{site.email}</a> or by telephone on
          <a href={telLandline}>{site.phoneLandline}</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
